      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T16:18:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this does not work for users that have different user names in @chromium.org and @google.com domains. Can we replace @google.com with @ instead? It would cover all emails that I currently see at https://luci-milo-dev.appspot.com/p/chromium/g/main/console",
      "revId": "0770d003f128c2581fbe1c637bdec83a11a98d94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9bf28d4_8a44bfe8",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/middleware.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 160,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T17:24:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What\u0027s the advantage of @ over @google.com?\n\nAs noted in https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id\u003d787595#c16, only ldaps have previously been displayed anyway to no ill effect. If, however, we are in fact worried about losing information between @chromium.org and @google.com, then we shouldn\u0027t strip the domain at all.",
      "parentUuid": "a95abe78_51fc69ab",
      "revId": "0770d003f128c2581fbe1c637bdec83a11a98d94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "637b5cdf_17bae28a",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/middleware.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 160,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T17:33:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the advantage of (replacing \"@google.com\" with \"@\" or \"\") over (stripping domain entirely) is that if foo@google.com is using bar@chromium.org and bar@chromium.org is a sheriff, we don\u0027t display ambiguous \"bar\". \n\nIf we strip domain only if it is @google.com, then we 1) still don\u0027t loose info 2) it is still short",
      "parentUuid": "a9bf28d4_8a44bfe8",
      "revId": "0770d003f128c2581fbe1c637bdec83a11a98d94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f438cf7f_255ef9ff",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/middleware.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 160,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T18:22:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK, we had a misunderstanding.\n\nI thought you meant to \u0027replace @google.com with @ instead of \"\"\u0027, not \u0027replace /only/ @google.com, with either @ or \"\"\u0027.\n\nI\u0027d prefer going with replacing @google.com with \"\", just because the concern in this bug is giving space to the builder summaries.\n\nNote that this won\u0027t look any different from the existing display, since all emails are @google.com.",
      "parentUuid": "637b5cdf_17bae28a",
      "revId": "0770d003f128c2581fbe1c637bdec83a11a98d94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
